description:
Hey everyone! Thanks for stopping by the channel. Tonight I made Shrimp Pasta - Creole Style. It is from the Publix Aprons Meals Recipe. It was really good and it was ready in 20 minutes. 
I already had a lot of the ingredients on hand. I only had to purchase the scampi sauce and the blackening seasoning. I find that recipe cooking can get a little expensive. Therefore, I will try to substitute some items or I try to plan ahead and add to my shopping list.
Give this recipe a try if you're  looking for something different to add to the menu! 
**** It is a little spicy. If you are not a fan of spice I would recommend leaving out the Red Pepper Flakes and less Blackening Seasoning. Here is the link to the recipe:
https://www.publix.com/recipe/creole-style-shrimp-saute

Hello friendsğŸ¤—, In this video, I want to teach you the best way to cook chicken feet stew.  You will learn how to cook spicy and delicious chicken feet

Ingredients for chicken feet food:
Chicken feet
Hot red sauce
soya sauce
Salt
Turmeric
Chopped onion
Chopped garlic
Oil
Black pepper
Chives
Sesame(for garnish)

0:00Introduction to the best way to cook chicken feet
0:30To prepare chicken feet stew, chop the onion
1:12To prepare the chicken feet, cut the nails
2:11Allow the chicken feet to cook well in the water that was already boiled along with bay leaf and onion
3:05Drain the cooked chicken feet
3:25To start cooking the delicious stew of chicken feet, pour oil into the pan and fry the chopped onion and add turmeric
4:17Add chopped garlic to the ingredients of chicken feet stew
4:39Add the cooked chicken feet to the ingredients
4:49Add soy sauce to the delicious chicken feet stew. The amount depends on you
5:38Add red hot sauce to chicken feet stew to get a unique taste
6:10Add some chopped chives to the chicken feet stew and let it cool
6:33The delicious stew of chicken feet is ready

title: ğŸ‡¹ğŸ‡­  BANGKOK'S BEST (AND ONE OF THE OLDEST) STREET FOOD MARKET || TALAT PHLU - A HIDDEN GEM ğŸ’
description:
In this video I take you to the street food markets in Talat Phlu in Bangkok.

I love the Talat Phlu neighborhood - and even more the food market there. Talat Phlu has one of the best, most authentic and oldest food markets in all of Bangkok! The food is varied, simply delicious and cheap! 
Tourists rarely visit the market. 
And the best: Not far away, there is even another market, which is also worth a visit: Tha Phra Open Air Market.

ğŸ‘‰ğŸ¼ So if you come to Bangkok - don't miss it!

The beautiful and laid-back neighborhood of Talat Phlu is located on the "other" side of the Chao Phraya river. It is an old neighborhood that has existed since the Thon Buri era, and is the locality for people of various nationalities, mainly Chinese, but also Muslims. The area is close to Talat Phlu BTS Station on the Silom Line of the BTS Skytrain and Pho Nimit and Wutthakat BTS Stations. Can also be reached by train.

I have been to both markets many times and have eaten varied delicious snacks and drinks (like the special Coca cola slushie - which honestly wasn't special at all.ğŸ¤«)
In this episode I take you to both markets and try with you crispy waffles, coconut pancakes, fried insects, cucumber salad and the best curry chicken. 

Unfortunately, on this day the stand with the 'Gui chai tod' was closed. If you go to the market, make sure to try these crispy little Chinese chive dumplings. Sooo good! 

You'll find everything your heart, or rather your stomach, desires here. 

P.S.: And yes, it was hot that day, very hot!ğŸ˜…

description:
Sa videong namang ito ay ituturo ko sa inyo ang Cheese Donut Recipe at aalamin din natin kung gaano nga ba kalaki ang pwede nating kitain dito. Kasama ko ding ituturo ang Iba't ibang paraan kung paano ito gagawaing patok na negosyo  sa harap ng ating bahay. Ituturo din natin ang tamang pag co-costing upang mapresyuhan natin ng wasto ang ating produkto. Bagay na bagay po ito para sa ating Sideline or Homebased Business.

Para po sa mga Misis na tulad ko na nagnanais makatulong sa ating Mister upang madagdagan ang ating budget kahit tayo ay nasa bahay lang at kapiling ang ating mga chikiting.

Bagay na bagay din po ito kahit tayo ay may trabaho na at nag nanais na magdagdagan ang ating income dahil madali lang siyang gawain at maganda ang kita kaya pwedeng-pwede nyo itong gawing sideline. Maaari nyo itong ipa-oder sa inyong mga kasamahan sa trabaho at siguradong hindi kayo mapapahiya sa lasa at sarap.

Gayun din naman sa mga mahal nating OFW na nagpaplano ng mag FOR GOOD NA DITO SA PINAS, maari nyo rin po itong isama sa inyong mga balak negosyuhin.

Basta't kailangan lang ng diskarte, sipag at tyaga at siguradong ito ay uunlad. Kaya Good Luck at Sana makatulong ang Video na ito sa inyo.

INGREDIENTS:

Donut Dough:
1/2 kl Flour
1/4 cup White Sugar(60gms)
50 gms Powdered Milk
1 tsp Yeast
1/2 tsp Salt
1 Large Egg
50 gms Butter or Margarine
270 ml Water or Milk

Fillings:
Cheese

Coating:
Powdered Sugar
Refined Sugar

title: The BEST STUFFED SALMON and SHRIMP ALFREDO!
description:
Ingredients:
Salmon
Peel and deveined shrimp (I use 13/15 count per pound)
1 pound of fettuccine pasta
1 bunch spinach
1 8oz package cream cheese (softened)
3 slices of bacon chopped up
1.5 cups Parmesan cheese (Freshly grate yourself if you can!)
1.5 cups asiago cheese (Freshly grate yourself if you can!)
1 quart half and half
4 oz butter (I prefer Kerry gold)
Grapeseed oil (to coat the salmon)

Seasonings used:
Old bay
Badia complete 
Garlic powder
Onion powder
Black pepper 
Smoked paprika 

Season shrimp and salmon to your liking. I used about a teaspoon of each on both the salmon and shrimp.

title: Asmr Jamaican Jerk Chicken Mukbang  No Talking  Asmr Foodie Eats
tags: "asmr,jerkchicken,Jamaican,Jamaicanjerkchicken,chickenwings,mukban"
description:
Jamaican Jerk Chicken Wings recipe to make your own spicy CHICKEN WINGS CHICKEN THIGHS or CHICKEN DRUMSTICKS. Amsr Whispering and No Talking Eating sounds Mukbang video. I hope you enjoy ğŸ˜‰

Please don't forget to like and Subscribe. I appreciate you being here.

JERK SAUCE RECIPEğŸ˜‹ 

3 Scotch bonnet peppers
1/2 cup of Vinegar
3/4 cup soya sauce
1 /2 cup of Cilantro
2 tbsp olive oil
2 tbsp orange juice
1 tbsp brown sugar
1/2 onion
3 cloves of garlic
1 tsp fresh ginger
1 lime, juice
1 tsp thyme
1 tsp Cinnamon
1 tsp Allspice
pinch salt

1. Wash the wings and drain
2. Squeeze the juice of half a lemon over top and marinade for 30 mins 
3. Pre-heat the oven to 400 f
4. Coat the wings in Jerk sauce and bake for 45 mins till cooked. 

Blend all together in your blender. Stores in a sealable container in the fridge up to 3 months.

title: UNIQUE Indonesian street food - BOGOR FOOD HEAVEN + Indonesian street food in Bogor, Indonesia
tags: "Indonesian street food,indonesian street food dessert,indonesian street food reaction,indonesian street food jelly,indonesian street food cooking,indonesian street food jakarta,unique indonesian street food,Indonesian street food bogor,street food in indonesia,bogor street food,bogor food,abroad and hungry,max ginestra,abroad and hungry indonesia,street food suryakencana bogor,indonesian street food tour in jakarta,indonesia street food,indonesian snacks,bogo"
description:
Indonesian street food - In this video, I will take you on an Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia.

To start our unique Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia, we went to a local food stall to try Toge Goreng for the first time.

To continue our Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia, we went to explore the traditional market where they sell lots of unique foods and we tried Jamu, a traditional Javanese drink.

Moving on with our unique Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia, for lunch we had the most insanely delicious meal in the city, Sop Buntut.

To continue our Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia, we had a unique soup that you cannot have anywhere else, Soto Kuning.

To end our unique Indonesian street food tour in Bogor, Indonesia, we had a very interesting and refreshing drink called Es Cincau and the Bogor-famous Asinan Buah.

Hope you enjoyed this Indonesian street food tour of Bogor.

Stay tuned for more street food videos like this.


LOCATIONS:

1-Toge Goreng IPB bang aldi
https://goo.gl/maps/EiXBvLbzp3Y72PPv6

2-Pasar Bogor Suryakencana
https://goo.gl/maps/z3814C2RMHHh56GUA

3-Sop Buntut Sapi Ma'Emun
https://goo.gl/maps/n8jQya2VUSqJpu7t7

4-Soto Kuning khas Bogor Pak Asep
https://goo.gl/maps/8Kv8RrMEnwL3sZi38

5-Asinan Ahauw Bogor
https://goo.gl/maps/nMZBmex9NngpJYUi8

SUBSCRIBE TO SUPPORT MY JOURNEY!  

  
Buongiorno guys, I'm Max Ginestra.  

I've always had a dream to travel for food around the world.   

I believe that through food we can deeply explore new cultures, traditions and get to know the people.  

In this channel, Abroad and Hungry, I will share my passion for street food, local and traditional cuisine.

RECIPES
Picarones: https://us.kiwilimon.com/recipe/desserts/peruvian-picarones

Muhogo Bhajia
Ingredients
350 grams cassava
120 grams potatoes
Turmeric Powder
Salt
Lemon
Sugar
Habanero chili
Ginger & Garlic paste
Coriander Leaves
Chilli Powder
(Add all spices as per your taste)
Directions 
Scrape the skin of the Cassava and grate it.
Boil the potatoes and mash them. Add all the spices to the potatoes and then mix it with the Cassava thoroughly. Make small balls and slightly press to flatten it a bit. Deep fry in hot oil and serve hot with Tamarind Chutney.


Potato Chap
Yield: 24 patties
Filling:
Â¼ lb ground beef (fat ratio: 85% to 15%)
Less than 1/4 bunch parsley, finely chopped
Â¼ medium yellow onion finely chopped
1 teaspoon (regular not measuring) seven spice
Salt and pepper to taste
Dough:
3 large russet potatoes (530gr) roughly
1 large egg
1 cup potato flakes
3 Tbsp and 2 tsp Cornstarch (start with 2 Tbsp, then slowly incorporate to see if you need the rest)
Â½ teaspoon turmeric 
Salt and pepper to taste
Oil for Frying
Directions
Boil your potato WITH THE SKIN ON in salted water until fork tender (this will help retain more of the starch for the dough). While the potato is boiling, you are going to start your filling. 
Cut your onions and parsley.
In a pan on medium heat, cook the onions with the ground beef.  Once the beef is cooked and browned, you are going to drain the residual oil.
Add seven spice, salt and pepper. 
Turn off your pan and add parsley and mix to let it cool.

Once the potatoes are fork tender, you are going to peel off the skins and mash them until smooth. They should be as smooth as possible (you do not want any chunks) and let them cool. 
Then you will add in salt, pepper, and turmeric and mix until smooth and the dough looks consistently yellow. Give it a taste and see if it needs more salt, then add your egg.
Add your potato flakes and mix.
You can let your dough sit for 1-2 hours in the refrigerator which probably helps increase the starch but I never have the patience. So here is where you can incorporate the cornstarch. 
I would start with two tablespoons of cornstarch. Initially the dough will be very powdery and break apart like mashed potatoes. Then when you keep incorporating more cornstarch, it will start to hold itâ€™s shape in a ball. 
Try to flatten it and see if it breaks when folding. If it does, keep incorporating more cornstarch adding half (measuring) teaspoons of cornstarch at a time. Mix the mixture and try forming the dough again. Trust the process, eventually it will turn out. I found mine came together after 3 tbp and 2 tsp and then I just let it sit for 30 minutes.
Once itâ€™s the consistency you want, take a tablespoon amount of the dough, flatten it into a circle (pressing with your fingers while rotating) and then grab a spoonful of the filling and fold the edges over and pinch until you have a patty. 
Press down gently to make sure there are no air pockets. If there are holes just use the dough mixture to patch it up and also you can put some water on your finger to remove creases.
You can fry them right away but to ensure no breakage, you can put them in the fridge, covered, for 30 minutes to an hour. 
Heat up oil on medium heat in a pot and once ready, you just need to fry and flip until the patty is golden brown. Which should take about 3- 5 minutes and then let them rest on a paper towel until you are ready to serve.

Mukbang,also know as eating show,

title: KOREAN STREET FOOD - Gwangjang Market Street Food Tour in Seoul South Korea | BEST Spicy Korean Food
tags: "korea,luke martin,korean street food,street food,food,korean food,street food korea,gwangjang,gwangjang market,seoul street food,seoul,south korea,seoul food,food vlog,spicy food,street food seoul,chopstick travel,seafood,korea seafood,taiwan,luke martin taiwan,street food south korea,market,korean market,traditional market,korean,try,korea 2017,2017,best street food,seoul vlog,korea vlog,seoul 2017,korean restaurant,kimch"
description:
Korean Street Food | Street Food in Seoul | Gwangjang Market

So PUMPED to be in Seoul, South Korea for a MASSIVE Street Food tour! We spent 7 days feasting on the best of Korean cuisine! We have 4 videos from Korea that we are so excited to show you guys, but we also filmed a lot that won't make the first channel so you can check that out on Luke Martin Raw - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCD5v3wL-6NMG0SMMeR6TxsA

Seoul is packed with SPICY Street Foods like the ones we tried at Gwangjang Market! We fell in love with Korean food very quickly! Stay tuned for the rest of our videos where we eat all kinds of Korean foods including some DELICIOUS seafood! 

========================================================
Hey there, my name's Luke Martin with www.chopsticktravel.com ! I'm on a journey to document the BEST Street Food around the world! The Chopstick Travelers are based in Taiwan, where we frequent the best Street Food stands everywhere from Taipei to Kaohsiung. Not only do we feast on amazing street food in Taiwan, but our food focused travels take us on Street Food missions trying unique foods in places like Japan, Malaysia, Korea and Hong Kong and around the world!

I post 2 times a week mostly food, some travel. Street Food tours around the world and the most unique dishes we can find in all kinds of hole-in-the-wall restaurants. Stay updated for my latest video VIA our Facebook page and Instagram!

- https://www.facebook.com/chopsticktravel/
- https://www.instagram.com/derpyluke/

Always remember that the best part of travel is immersing yourselves in the local culture, and no where better can you immerse yourself than into the Street Food!

Jamaican Rasta Pasta
tags: "Rasta Pasta,side dish,vegetarian side dish,alfredo pasta,jamaican rasta pasta,live life loving you,quick meal,15 min dinner,20 min dinner recipe,jerk chicke"
description:
In this video, you will learn how to make Rasta Pasta using simple ingredients that can be found in your local grocery store. This recipe can be made in less than 15 minutes and will be a hit with your family and friends. It's perfect for a quick dinner or a side dish for an event. This dish can be paired with any kind of seafood or meat. My apologies for the noisy background. My babies like to sing :) Thank you for watching. If you enjoyed this video, please make sure to Like and Subscribe.

You will need the following:

1 box of Ronzoni Penne Rigate No. 76 Pasta
3 to 4 teaspoons of Walkerwood Traditional Jamaican Jerk Seasoning (Mild)
1 jar (15 oz) of Classico Creamy Alfredo
1 jar (15 oz) of Classico Four Cheese Alfredo
4 halves Sweet Bell Peppers (yellow, orange, red and green)
2 garlic cloves finely chopped
1/2 tsp black pepper powder
1/2 tsp dried pasley
1/4 tsp red pepper flakes (omit if giving to kids, very spicy)
1/2 tsp onion powder
oil for sauteing

title: Super Stable Cake Frosting Using Condensed Milk | Icing & Frosting What's The Difference?
tags: "tipid tips atbp Cake Frosting using condensed milk,Negosyo idea sa maliit na puhunan,paano maggawa ng Stable Frosting Icing,ingredients for Cake Frosting,recipe for Cake Frosting Icing,Sideline/Homebased Business Cake Frosting Icing,madaling paraan ng paggawa ng masarap na Cake Frosting Icing,panlasang pinoy Cake Frosting,yummy kitchen Cake Frosting,easiest way To Make Cake Frosting,Vanilla Frosting Icing,Chocolate Frosting Icing,Difference between Frosting and Icin"
description:
Sa videong ito ituturo ko naman sa inyo ang madaling paraan ng paggagawa ng Super Stable Cake Frosting Using Condensed Milk. Bagay na bagay ito lalo na ngayong mainit ang panahon upang hindi malusaw agad ang Frosting ng ating cakes or cupcakes. Maggagawa tayo ng 2 flavors (Vanilla Frosting/White & Pink, at Chocolate Frosting). Ide Design din natin ito sa ating Cake and Cupcake upang maipakita natin kung gaano ba siya ka stable. Ipapaliwanag din natin sa videong ito kung ano nga ba ang pinagkaiba ng icing sa frosting.

Maaari po natin itong gamiting pang substitute sa Icing or sa ating Chocolate syrup na ginamit para sa ating Super Moist Chocolate Cake upang magkaron ng variant ang ating produkto.

Hangad ko na makatulong ang videong ito sa mga Nanay na nag-uumpisa sa kanilang maliit na negosyo. Basta kailangan lang ng Sipag, Tyaga At Diskarte at Siguradong Tayo ay Aasenso. Good Luck And God Bless po sa ating Lahat.

INGREDIENTS:
Vanilla Frosting:

400gms Butter
1 can Condensed Milk (390gms)
150gms Vegetable Shortening(Lard)
1tsp Vanilla Flavor
Gel Color(Chef Master) Any Desired Color

Chocolate Frosting
200gms Butter
1/2 can Condensed Milk (195gms)
75gms Vegetable Shortening(Lard)
2tbps Cocoa Powder (Bensdorp)
1tbsp Instant Coffee (Nescafe)

title: ITO NA YATA ANG NEGOSYONG TUTUBO KA NG MALAKI SA APAT NA INGREDIENTS LAMANG â‰ï¸â—
tags: "negosyo recipe,negosyong maliit ang puhunan malaki ang kita,negosyong patok ngayon,negosyong dinadagsa ng customer ngayon,100 pesos puhunan pangnegosyo,patok na negosyo,patok na negosyo ngayon,patok na negosyo ngayong pandemic,patok pangnegosyo,saba recipe,banana recipe,business ide"
description:
Haler mga ka kusina!

Bagong negosyo recipe na naman ang pwede ninyong lutuin at pagkakitaan. Narito ang mga sangkap pati na rin ang costing.

NOTE:ğŸ“¢
Paalala lang po, ito po ay basi sa mga nagastos ko lamang SA MGA INGREDIENTS NA NAGAMIT KO. MAAARING MAGKAIBA ANG PRESYO NG INGREDIENTS SA LUGAR NINYO AT DITO SA AMIN. Think before you click sa mga comments ninyo..good vibes lang po tayo dito.

Ingredients:

1 kilo (9 pcs) Saba Banana (Too ripe) - 25.00
3 & 1/2 cups All-purpose Flour - 12.00
1/2 bar Cheese - 15.00
2 packs Crispy Fry Seasoned Bread Crumbs - 36.00
Oil - 15.00
Electricity - 6.00
Total: P109.00

Yields: 45 pieces
Suggested Selling Price: P5.00 each
Computation:
45 Ã— 5.00 = 225.00
Less Puhunan: 109.00
TUBO: P116.00
Monthly Income: P3,480.00

Note:
P'wede pang magdagdag ng 1/2 cup ng harina kung basa pa masyado ang dough. Depende kasi 'yan sa saging na mabibili mo. Kung sobrang hinog, mas basa s'ya kapag naluto.

Kung araw-araw magluluto at magbebenta,maaaring kumita ng hanggang P3,480.00 sa isang buwan. Tandaan, hanggat masipag ka, ikaw ay aasenso!
Mas mainam na magluto ka ng  maramihan sapagkat mas maraming lulutuin mas malaki ang iyong kikitain..

Pwede n'yo pang bawasan o dagdagan ang presyo depende kung magkano ang inyong naging puhunan.
Hindi ko isinama sa costing ang  gastos sa labor, transpo at ang exact cost ng electricity dahil maaaring mabawasan/madagdagan pa d'yan ang puhunan kung sakali. Kaya, paalala lang po, kayo pa rin ang masusunod.

title: $10 FILIPINO STREET FOOD TOUR at UGBO in TONDO Manila, Philippines ğŸ‡µğŸ‡­ | MUKBANG Philippines
tags: "street food philippines,filipino street food,ugbo tondo,philippines street food,manila street food,tondo manila,philippines food,street food,ugbo tondo street food,ugbo tondo night market,ugbo tondo street food location,ugbo street tondo manila,mukbang philippines,famous filipino street food,bags packed family,bag packed family,backpack family,pinoy mukbang,filipino food,filipino mukbang,mukbang,mukbang philippines street food,philippines food tou"
description:
If you want off-the-beaten-path Filipino street food, with a more local (less touristy) feel, head to UGBO in the Tondo District of Manila. This place was busy with a younger crowd, with lots of music and action going on. The entire street is just one food vendor after another. We really only spent time on this one street, so Iâ€™m sure we missed a lot, as well. We were able to get a taxi here and back to our hotel with no problem. There were many tuk-tuk trucks passing through there, too. We never figured out how to get on one of those, so that is something we will have to try when we come back. In this video, we eat, eat, and eat some more. We had fried foods, meat on a stick, popcorn, empanadas, and the dessert YOU suggested: Halo Halo! Kelly found a twister potato (and off camera she found fresh chili and garlic peanuts). It was a full night of eating. We met so many fun kids running around. 

We love that YOU get to join us around the world. The Bags Packed Family community has grown so much over the last few months and we appreciate all of your support. Stick with us as we explore more of the Philippines, heading to Cebu and Palawan soon.

If you like videos like this please LIKE and SUBSCRIBE. SHARE this video with someone who loves exploring the world, traveling, and/or traveling with kids. All of these things help us know which videos you want us to make while supporting our channel.

In this Chinese street food tour of Chengdu, China, we're bringing you to eat at 4 classic Chengdu foods. Chinese cooking is some of the best in the world, and in Chengdu, China, the cuisine is world famously known as Sichuan cuisine or Szechuan cuisine. It is spicy and numbing and covered in delicious Chili oil. I moved here to Chengdu specifically to be able to eat spicy and delicious Chinese street foods. 

â–ºFor addresses a full Chengdu Food Tour, visit my blog post on Chengdu street food, it has a huge list of the best street foods to try in Chengdu, China. The Chengdu food guide features all of the locations within this Chinese street food video: â–ºhttps://www.thefoodranger.com/the-ultimate-chengdu-food-tour/

In this Chinese street food tour video, we're starting out with one of China's most famous foods; DUMPLINGS. In Chengdu, they are different from the rest of China. Here, they are boiled and covered in a thick and spicy chili oil that leaves you so SATISFIED! These are some of the most satisfying dumplings ever! I must admit though, the filling could have been more plump. If you are traveling to Chengdu to eat Szechuan cuisine, I would personally recommend trying the red chili oil wontons first. 

And after those amazing dumplings in Chengdu, we're eating another famous dish in Sichuan cuisine, RABBIT. Eating rabbit is very famous in Sichuan, and here in Chengdu, locals love it in a numbing and spicy Szechuan Sauce. But we wanted to try a more UNIQUE style of eating rabbit in Sichuan, on top of noodles. So we visited a local rabbit noodle joint and ate a couple unique bowls of Chinese Sichuan noodles. The first was the rabbit noodles, where the rabbit is served to you in thin slices covered in chilies, ginger, and onions. You then pour it over top of your thick and spicy chili oil broth noodle bowl. It was absolutely delicious. The next bowl of spicy noodles that we ordered was the beef noodle soup - red braised beef noodle soup. Super delicious and spicy!

After eating those 2 bowls of delicious Sichuan noodles, we are bringing you to a nice original fly restaurant of Chengdu, Mingting fandian. The fly restaurants of Chengdu are old locations that are sometimes less than cleanly but have incredible food! Nowadays most fly restaurants in Chengdu are actually really clean and you don't have to worry about getting sick from eating the street food. At mingting restaurant, we ordered a river carp,  spicy pork blood, spare ribs, fried sticky rice strips, Sichuan sausages, twice cooked pork, and pig brain tofu. It was all incredibly delicious!

And for our final meal in this Chinese street food tour of Chengdu, China, we're going for one of the most famous foods to try in Sichuan, HOT POT! We found a local 9 section hot pot that serves spicy and delicious hot pot and is always busy! For detailed addresses to these restaurants and street foods, make sure to visit my full Chinese food guide to Chengdu, China:

China has so many amazing street foods to try, and I've been filming and documenting them for you for the past 4 years. In my opinion, the best noodle dish in China is dan dan noodles, right here in Chengdu, Sichuan. China has some of the best street food around the world, and these dan dan noodles were INSANELY GOOD, some of the best noodles in China for sure!

If you're traveling to China to eat and try different street foods, and perhaps want to learn a little bit about Chinese food and chinese cooking in the process, you need to try a few different variations of Dan Dan noodles. When they prepare the traditional Chinese dan dan noodle recipe right on the street, you can watch as they scoop the main ingredients like chili oil, soy sauce, sichuan peppercorn, and garlic right into the noodle bowl and then place the steaming hot noodles right over top. It's truly satisfying! After they put the noodles over top, they place their signature fried ground pork on top, known in Chinese as shaozi. 

When your dan dan noodles arrive to your table, it is very important to mix up all the chili oil and all of the ingredients throughout. This ensures that the flavour and the hot oil gets coated onto each noodle before you take a bite. It's also quite satisfying mixing the noodles and watching the dark red oil slowly turn each noodle from white into red and silky smooth. 

When you take your first bite, you'll understand why this is one of the BEST Chinese street foods you need to try. The spicy noodles are coated with an incredibly aromatic chili oil and really send you straight up to heaven! It's one of the best forms of Chinese cooking!

title: MASAK AYAM NAPINADAR TANPA GOTTA (DARAH)
description:
#ayamnapinadar #anakkost #khasbatak

Bahan :
Satu kg ayam kampung muda
Setengah kelapa parut
Garam 2 sdt
Jeruk nipis 3 buah

Bahan bumbu halus yg disangrai :
Batang serei 3 buah
Lengkuas 5 cm, kupans & potong potong
Jahe 7 cm, kupas & potong potong
Kunyit 5 cm
Bawang putih 5 siung
Bawang merah 20 siung
Cabai merah 20 buah
Kemiri 10 buah

Bumbu halus yg tidak disangrai :
Andaliman sesuai selera
Cabai rawit 15 buah
 
Cara Membuat: 
1. Ayam disembelih, dibului, dipotong 4 bagian, dan campurkan garam & 2 buah jeruk nipis, kemudian dibakar tanpa bumbu hingga matang. Kemudian potong potong lagi menjadi bagian yg lebih kecil/dicincang.

2. Sangrai atau bakar semua bumbu yang disangrai, kemudian giling semua bumbu yang disangrai ditambah dengan bumbu halus yang tidak disangrai.

3. Sangrai kelapa parut sampai cokelat kehitaman, kemudian haluskan sampai keluar minyak.

4 Tumis semua bumbu, jika sudah wangi masukkan ayam, aduk sampai merata, kemudian masukkan kelapa yg sudah dihaluskan. Tambahkan air sedikit dan garam secukupnya.
Aduk sampai bumbu merata dan meresap.

5. Siap disajikan

title: Visit Royal Warsaw in Elmwood Park NJ For Terrific Polish Food & Fun
tags: "Elmwood Park NJ,Savory Pixels,Polish Food,Pierogi,Kielbasa,Stuffed Cabbag"
description:
I've never had Polish food before. 
It's not in my experience. So I jumped at the chance to visit Royal Warsaw Restaurant in Elmwood Park, New Jersey. I'm glad I went-now I have a standard which to compare other Polish restaurants.
Royal Warsaw  has an extensive menu of Polish favorites. I sampled pierogi, kielbasa, stuffed cabbage, sauerkraut and a pork loin. Everything at Royal Warsaw is homemade, on site. There is love and care in everything they make. It's like eating at Grandma's.
Be sure to get the pierogies. They appear as both fried and steamed as  appetizers, in mixed platters and dessert pierogies, which are filled with berries and are like fruit dumplings. Messy and delicious-save room!
If you don't think you like sauerkraut, try it here. Homemade on site, it's delicious, cooked with subtle spices. You'll be a convert.Royal Warsaw is located on a main road , easy to access from anywhere. There is plenty of parking onsite. Some nights are karaoke-come and hear the standards belted out in Polish for a truly fun night out.

tags: "Pork curry,Manipuri,Pork,Oksha thongb"
description:
Oksha thongba (pork meat curry) in Manipuri style, please enjoy!!!

Available in Amazon.in
Meat cutting wooden block https://amzn.to/3qe5LwF
Heiribob https://amzn.to/3dlE5Df
Hawkins Frying Pan https://amzn.to/3BnkUlP
Pressure Cooker https://amzn.to/3BaAcdp
Gas Stove https://amzn.to/3CTQ3hB
Machal (Manipuri spices) https://amzn.to/3enIANv
Skimmer (Khabei) https://amzn.to/3enIJ3v
Kitchen Scissor https://amzn.to/3RzuhDV
Spice containers https://amzn.to/3TVb4yt

Ingredients: 
Pork meat (oksha asemba); Onion; garlic; ginger; red potato; jeera; Culantro (Awa phadigom); Coriander leaves; Sichuan seeds (Mukthrubi maru); Spring onion; Manipuri spices (Machal); King Chilli (U-morok); Pakchoi; Red Chilli powder (morok machu).

Local Jodhpur pork are available at this location: https://maps.app.goo.gl/q7mFt6yDxcM6t...

Kindly visit 7-SISTER SHOPPEE, for various North-East spices and vegetables available at reasonable prices: https://goo.gl/maps/FDDb3LU1iwmCbnZcA

VIDEO was captured using iPhone SE (2020)

tags: "banana,banana bread,banana loaf,banana loaf bread,mai goodnes banana bread,mai goodness banana loaf,easy banana bread,soft and moist banana bread,pinoy bread,filipino bread,lacatan bananas,lacatan,banana bread recipe,banana bread ingredients,how to make banana loaf bread,how to make banana loaf,banana loaf ingredients and instructions,how to bake banana loaf,loaf bread,banana loaf bread for business,costing,banana bread costing,home baking busines"
description:
Freshly baked banana Loaf Bread for breakfast or merienda partnered with coffee or tea. Better than store bought and can be made easily at home as it includes simple and complete instructions for first time bakers. Enjoy the soft and moist banana bread anytime of the day! Best for your home base baking business!

Banana Loaf Bread

Wet Ingredients:
â€¢ 3/4 cup brown sugar - P7.50
â€¢ 1/2 cup vegetable oil or canola or corn oil - P11.00
â€¢ 2 Large Egg - P15.00
â€¢ 1 tbsp banana extract - P2.00
â€¢ 3 big (300g) over ripe lacatan bananas  - P20.00 (it can be cheaper if it's over ripe)

Dry Ingredients:
â€¢ 1 2/3 cups all purpose flour - P10.00
â€¢ 1/2 tsp iodized salt - P1.00
â€¢ 1 1/2 tsp baking powder - P2.00
â€¢ 1/2 tsp baking soda - P1.00
â€¢ 1 tsp cinnamon powder - P3.00

Toppings 1:
â€¢ Chocolate chips - P10.00
â€¢ Almonds or walnuts or cashew or any nuts - P10.00


Toppings 2:
â€¢ Glazed fruit - P10.00 
â€¢ Cherries - P10.00

*Preheat oven for 15 minutes at 180â°C.
*Bake for approximately 40 to  50 minutes or until the stick test comes out clean and then halfway through the baking at 20 minutes, turn the baking pan around for even cooking. If your oven has a fan to circulate the heat, then no need to turn the pan around.
*Double the measurements if you want to make more.

Note: 
The ingredients are listed according to the sequence on how you are going to mix it.

Baking Pan you need:
2 loaf pans 7in x 3.5in or 8x3 inches

Costing:
Cost of Ingredients - P90.50
Overhead Cost (40% of ingredients costs for lpg, elec, water, fare etc) - P36.20 
Total Costing: P126.70 (exclusive of packaging)
Yields - 2 loaves (7x3 inches or 8x3 inches loaf)
Net Cost of each loaf - P63.35 (exclusive of packaging) x 1.7 (tubo) = P107.70

Selling price per loaf  - P100.00 or P120.00 with packaging

description:
Resep Ayam : Bakso Ayam Oseng Pedas - Spicy Chicken Meatballs ala Pancarasa Cooking


Bahan adonan Bakso:
500 gr Dada Ayam fillet
1 siung Bawang Putih
1 sdt Merica bubuk
1 sdm Garam
100 gr Tepung Tapioka
Sedikit Soda Kue
Penyedap Rasa secukupnya
Air secukupnya

Bumbu Oseng-oseng :
4 siung Bawang Merah
1 siung Bawang Putih
2 Cabai Merah
Cabai Rawit sesuai selera
2 sdm Gula
1 sdt Garam
1 sdm Kecap Manis
Penyedap Rasa secukupnya
Air secukupnya




Meatball dough Ingredients :
500 gr Chicken Breast fillets
1 clove of Garlic
1 tsp Pepper powder
1 tbsp Salt
100 gr Tapioca Flour
